title: The Howell Book of Dogs: The Definitive Reference to 300 Breeds
description:
The Howell Book of Dogs is a [s]hardcover[/s], four-color book that will serve as a timeless reference for dog owners and those who are considering getting a dog. Approximately 300 breeds are covered, encompassing the AKC, UKC, and breeds not recognized by these two kennel clubs, such as the American Pit Bull Terrier. One or more color photographs of each breed supplement text that describes the breed's origins, physical characteristics, and personality traits. In addition, the book includes a section about dog care and training, making it the only reference book dog owners will ever need.

More details
The Howell Book of Dogs: The Definitive Reference to 300 Breeds and Varieties
